task.summary: First experimentation of new GUI using PyQt4
Reformatted code for readability and to adhere to current python conventions.
First attempt at connecting PyQt GUI to main keyboard.py code. Up to this point, only the initialization of the clocks, histogram (including updates), space-bar events, and text output are connected.
First fully-working GUI with PyQt. Code is still rough--will clean in later commit.
Fixed issue with undoing 'Delete', added undo text, stylized pause feature

1) delay on clock hands fixed -- no more bimodal distribution 2) text box un-editable and focus automatically shifted back to keyboard 3) layout in perfect grid with equal clock size 4) radar trails added 5) working windows executable in dist folder

--Added menu-bar, multiple clock design options, reinforcement color on default clock (as suggested in GNomon paper), improvements to layout. --executable mostly works, but has a few bugs--will fix for next commit (run keyboard.py for now)

--splash screen and welcome screen for first run --shell window and GUI for pre-training addition --new clocks including progress bar --text alignment control --QWERTY keyboard option --profanity filter for younger users under tools --high contrast mode under view
--timeout of 15 sec for deletion of erroneous clicks --clear screen clock --text entry rate label --check marks on menu selections --font size option --new chars: !?',. --new corpus from keith
updated saving pickles on training histogram
--new pretraining design to better simulate actual nomon interface --auto text sizing in the clocks to better display longer words --option to retrain in tool menu
--new branch to work on with tiffany
--first attempt to speed up clock drawing
first attempt to make drawing clocks faster pickles fixed for installer new working installer
